from sklearn import neighbors, model_selection, metrics
model = neighbors.KNeighborsClassifier(5)
xval = model_selection.KFold(10, shuffle=True)
scorer = metrics.make_scorer(metrics.cohen_kappa_score)
result = model_selection.cross_validate(model, X, y, scoring=scorer, cv=xval,
    return_train_score=True, return_estimator=True)
result

print('Test kappa mean:', result['test_score'].mean())
print('Test kappa SD:', result['test_score'].std())
print('Train kappa mean:', result['train_score'].mean())

means = []
for k in range(1, 200):
    model = neighbors.KNeighborsRegressor(k)
    xval = model_selection.KFold(10, shuffle=True)
    result = model_selection.cross_validate(model, reg_X[features], reg_y, cv=xval, scoring='r2',
        return_train_score=True)
    new_mean_score = result['test_score'].mean()
    means.append(new_mean_score)

In [ ]:
prediction = reg_y.mean()
errors = reg_y - prediction
errors
squared_errors = errors ** 2
squared_errors
mse = squared_errors.mean()
mse

mse_values = []
uniq_values = sorted(reg_X.s5.unique())
for split_point in uniq_values[1:]:
    subset_below = reg_y[reg_X.s5 < split_point]
    subset_above = reg_y[reg_X.s5 >= split_point]
    prediction_below = subset_below.mean()
    prediction_above = subset_above.mean()
    mse_below = ((subset_below - prediction_below) ** 2).mean()
    mse_above = ((subset_above - prediction_above) ** 2).mean()
    weighted_mse = (mse_below * len(subset_below) + mse_above * len(subset_above)) / (
        len(subset_above) + len(subset_below))
    mse_values.append(weighted_mse)

plt.figure(dpi=100)
plt.plot(uniq_values[1:], mse_values)
plt.xlabel('Cutoff value')
plt.ylabel('MSE at cutoff')

Text(0, 0.5, 'MSE at cutoff')
